<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1935-09-28T04:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1935-09-28T04:00:00-05:00" n="539" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d539">
                                <note rend="inline" type="source">765.84/1442: Telegram</note>
                                <head>
                                    <hi rend="italic">The Consul at Geneva</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Gilbert</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                                            State</gloss>
                                    </hi>
                                </head>
                                <opener>
                                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                                        <placeName>
                                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Geneva</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1935-09-28T10:00:00+01:00">September 28, 1935—10 a.m.</date>
                                        <lb/> [Received September 28—8:15 a.m.]</dateline>
                                </opener>
                                <p>389. Consulate’s 386, September 27, 5 p.m.<note n="85" xml:id="d539fn85">Not printed; but see Consulate’s telegram
                                        No. 376, September 26, 10 a.m., <ref target="#pg_658">p.
                                            658</ref>.</note>
                                </p>
                                <p>2. The following telegram was sent last night by the Secretary
                                    General to the Emperor of Ethiopia.</p>
                                <quote rend="blockquote">
                                    <p>“Committee of the Council has taken note of Your Majesty’s
                                        decision to withdraw Ethiopian troops to 30 kilometres from
                                        the frontier and appreciates the spirit in which this
                                        decision has been taken. The Committee, considering with the
                                        most careful attention your request for despatch of
                                        impartial observers, is examining whether the actual
                                        circumstances would permit them to discharge their
                                        mission.”</p>
                                </quote>
                                <closer>
                                    <signed>
                                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Gilbert</hi>
                                    </signed>
                                </closer>
                            </div>
                            </body></text></TEI>